For long generations you can use either context options, or the original long gen method, which is activated when frame_window_size is smaller than total frames(num_frames). When using this method the window size stays constant, extra frames are generated in the case the last window is cut short.

When using context options, set num_frames and frame_window_size to be equal, or you will get 'context_options are not compatible or necessary with WanAnim looping, since it creates the video in a loop' error.

Otherwise set frame_window_size to something the model is capable of doing normally, original default is 77, 81 seems to work too.

Original method is probably better for motion etc, and is faster, but the benefit of context windows is that it doesn't degrade over time on long clips.

widgets_values:
1. model base precision must not be bp16.

3. supports ≤ 81 frames only but got long video gen method.

This node makes the sampling into a loop to process all the needed frames. Each window is the same size, if the frame count doesn't divide evenly the audio will be padded with silence and extra frames generated.

Between each window the frames have to be re-encoded, thus no latents are saved and end result is already decoded.

You can also set an output_path to save each window's result as images during the process.
